@page "/about"

<PageTitle>PaycheckCalc — About</PageTitle>

<h1>About PaycheckCalc Web</h1>

<section class="card">
    <p>
        <strong>PaycheckCalc</strong> is a payroll calculator that runs entirely in your browser.
        It uses the same calculation engine (<code>PaycheckCalc.Core</code>) as the Android and
        Windows desktop apps, with no server-side processing of your inputs.
    </p>

    <h2>Currently available on the Web</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Single-paycheck calculation: gross → federal, FICA, state, locality → net.</li>
        <li>All 50 states + DC, including specialty calculators (CA Method B, OK OW-2, AR DFA,
            CO DR-0004, CT TPG-211, DE percentage method, AL annualized, IL flat, PA flat).</li>
        <li>Schema-driven state and locality input forms — every state contributes its own fields.</li>
        <li>Saved paychecks stored in your browser's <code>localStorage</code>, with JSON
            export/import that round-trips through the desktop and mobile heads
            (file name: <code>saved_paychecks.json</code>).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Not yet ported to the Web</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Annual Form 1040 projection flow (jobs &amp; YTD, other income, credits,
            quarterly estimates, what-if). Available in the desktop/mobile apps.</li>
        <li>Self-Employment / Schedule SE / QBI flow.</li>
        <li>Side-by-side scenario comparison.</li>
        <li>Address-based locality lookup (geocoding).</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        These flows are being added incrementally. Until then, run the desktop or
        Android build for full parity.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    <p>
        Nothing you enter is sent over the network. The site is a static
        WebAssembly bundle: once loaded, calculations and storage stay on your
        device.
    </p>
</section>
